cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with a computational model for object perception based on unsupervised learning and predictive approach. It involves processing the unsupervised interaction of an artificial agent with its environment to identify spatio-temporally invariant structures. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves processing sensory data, which is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV). The experiments involve an agent interacting with an environment, which is related to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves building an internal model, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
